Title: Necessity is the Mother of Invention Ep.2
SubTitle: No Translation

Text: A perfect...theory...

Seated at a desk covered in all manner of things,
Eta is wholeheartedly absorbed in her research...
...when another young girl approaches the lab.
Not again! Eta hasn't been eating her meals!
The soup's cold, the bread stale...it's such a waste.

I'm sure it was Gamma who brought it all here,
but she just doesn't know how to handle Eta.

Eta's not the kind of girl who will just eat whatever
food is left out for her.
Eta, I'm coming in.

Epsilon, another of the Seven Shadows, enters the
lab through the open door.

I completed my mission ahead of time. Lady Alpha
only had good things to say.
...That so?
And she also asked me to come check on you.

Good timing, she said, as Gamma wouldn't be able
to check if you've finished your food, having been
sent off on a mission herself.

That aside, I see that this room hasn't changed at
all. I keep telling you to tidy it even a tiny bit...but
there's just no point, is there?

I know you like things as they are, but you could at
least flip the table back over.
Hmmm...

And all these papers scattered about... Do you
actually need them?
Yeah... I do.

The papers in question are the very ones that had
been piled up on the upended table. They'd been
in order, of course...
Oh? There're numbers on them.
...Arrange them.
No way. Do it yourself.
Just do it yourself.
...Fine. If I have time.
Hm?

Completely focused on her work, Eta does not so much
as raise her head even as Epsilon approaches.
But that fact does not bother the latter.
Yikes! Your hair is an absolute mess!
Did you just roll out of bed?
Hmmm...
Epsilon runs some of Eta's hair through her fingers.

It's not greasy though. Seems like you're washing
it, at least.
Mm... Lady Alpha did...yesterday...forcefully...

...I see. Which means that it was bad enough that
Lady Alpha had to resort to using force.

You really should pay more attention to your
appearance...or rather, to living at least the
bare resemblance of a proper life.

I mean, what would happen to you if I was sent
on a long-term mission?
It'd all...work out somehow.
You really believe that?!

As they go back and forth Epsilon continues her
efforts to comb out the knots in Eta's hair, but
finds herself making no progress whatsoever.
Didn't Lady Alpha dry your hair after she washed it?
Well...I told her...I could do it...myself.
But you didn't, did you?
My research...needed me...
*sigh* I give up.

Are you really suggesting that the few minutes it
would have taken to dry your hair would have
affected your research that much? You really
need to think about yourself more.

Despite the grumbling, Epsilon's fingers are gentle
as they comb through Eta's hair.

Looks like I can't do much with just my fingers.
Hmm... Where's that comb gone...
Comb...?

I brought one along before and left it here, remember?
One with nice, wide teeth. Using a fine-toothed comb
to untangle hair would only cause you lots of pain.
I can't find it... I wonder where it could be.
I think, I left it over here...
Please...don't move the stuff...on the desk around.
Geez! Just where has it gone?!

Ugh... Really, please don't...move them around.
I remember...where everything is.

But Epsilon keeps moving the research papers,
organizing them in piles as she goes.
Eta finally makes a move.
Here...

She deftly extends a slime and picks up the comb from
the edge of the desk, passing it to Epsilon.
Oh, so that's where it was. Thanks.
Sure.

Nodding, Eta returns to her research. With comb in
hand, Epsilon also returns to untangling the former's
hair.

I can't believe you were able to find anything on
this desk, given the state it's in.
I just know...where everything is.
So please...don't clean anything...without asking.
Then you should tidy up for yourself.
Ugh... It's fine...this way.

Honestly? How can you look at this mess and say that
with a straight face?

It's not just the deskthe table's flipped over,
there's no space to put your feet, even the bed
is piled high with books and discarded clothes.
You're gonna get a scolding sooner or later.
From...Lady Alpha?
Right, from Lady Alpha herself.
Ugh...

When she is finally able to slide the comb through
Eta's hair without any resistance, Epsilon's hands
stop moving.
Where should I put this comb?
...Over there.

Eta raises her head and points to the edge of the
desk.
Make sure you don't lose it.
...Got it...
Alright. I'll get your food warmed up again.
Sure.

Eta's responses are starting to sound as if she is on
auto-pilotprobably because her focus has shifted
back to her research.

The bread is stale, but you'll be fine if it's warmed
up and got something spread on it, right? Butter,
maybe?
Sure.
Eta nods her head.

Since she's used to how Eta operates, Epsilon never
gets mad no matter how unresponsive the former gets.
I'll come by again later.

And with that, she deftly navigates her way through
the messy floor to the door and beyond.
And to make it possible...without a direct path...
No wobbling...stability...a rickety path...using slimes...
Loud...operational noise...out of the question...

Buried in her research and mumbling to herself,
Eta does not even turn her head to say goodbye.
